fi.helsinki.cs.turridevelop.util
Class ByNameContainer<T extends ByNameStored>

java.lang.Object
  fi.helsinki.cs.turridevelop.util.ByNameContainer<T>

public class ByNameContainer<T extends ByNameStored>
extends Object

Container that stores elements of type T by their names and tracks their name changes. Does not allow two elements to have the same name.

nameChanged

public void nameChanged(String old_name)
Function used by elements to notify when their names change.

Parameters:
old_name - The old name of the element.
Throws:
RuntimeException - if there was no element with name old_name or the new name is in use. This should not happen because ByNameStored objects should check the availibility with hasElement before calling.
